      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oh!! Actually this is one of the other reasons I choose rune over byte before. But I was reading utf-8 encoding (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTF-8) yesterday (since the grammar is designed to support utf-8 quoted string), and I have learned that an ascii byte will never show up in multiple byte sequence for a unicode code point. That\u0027s why I use `IndexByte` here and it should be safe unless user intentionally provide invalid byte in a utf-8 encoded string (I\u0027ve also tested this scenario and it turns out IndexRune will yield the same result as IndexByte: https://play.golang.org/p/85aMaqUzX-I). \n\nI\u0027ve switched to `IndexRune` in the latest patchset to keep consistent with other cases where they are iterating over Rune.",
